text:
My mother killed her little son;
118:118	F:F	F:H	the mother shut her eyes and her ears, that she might see and hear nothing, but there was a roaring sound in her ears like that of a violent storm, and in her eyes a burning and flashing like lightning:
119:119	N:N	N:H	My father grieved when I was gone;
120:120	H:H	H:H	Look, mother," said the man, "at the beautiful bird that is singing so magnificently; and how warm and bright the sun is, and what a delicious scent of spice in the air!"
